tarakihi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a fine-eating fish common in New Zealand waters, the jackass fish of southern Australia. <i>Dactylopagrus macropterus</i> (formerly <i>Chilodactylus</i>), a fine food fish
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: incl terakihi, common spelling error
